2.00	(Loneliness_Made_Me_Realize)_It's_You_That_I_Need	(Loneliness Made Me Realize) It's You That I Need	"(Loneliness Made Me Realize) It's You That I Need" is a 1967 hit single recorded by The Temptations for the Gordy label and produced by Norman Whitfield. This is one of the small handful of pre-psychedelic era songs the group recorded that had more than two members singing lead at one point, and the only one that charted. It peaked on the Billboard Hot 100 Pop charts in the Top 20 at number 14, and in the Billboard R&amp;B charts at number 3.	
